reenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_exclamation_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Yetis</span><hr size=1> This camp was great. I arrived here at level 39 and spent less than two days /played between level 39 and 44. Following the advice of the posters here, this is what I did:<br>
<br>
Bound myself near the entrance to the cave but far enough to where I could camp out if I had to(never had to, should have bound myself at the spires for a quicker Nexus sell port). I would start my grind by checking to make sure the cave wasn't camped. If so, I would summon the best fire pet I could get. The 36, 38 and 40 hitter fire pets do just fine here. I summon focus items, phantom plate, Spear of Warding and Dagger of Symbols for the pet. While I am summoning stuff at the beginning, I let the pet solo individual spawns while I med up. Usually the yeti needs one shock spell to bring it down or else the pet bites it if it is soloing.<br>
<br>
Once I am good to go, soloing the yeti camp is cake. I don't pull OUT of any rooms since these yetis aren't social - meaning you can be fighting a yeti pretty close to another yeti and it won't help - I just walk up to the yeti's spawn and /pet attack them. I BOII my pet and have it attack the next available spawn. I usually cast Lava Bolt or whatever the best bolt spell is named when the Yeti is at 80% health and again at 40% health. This will get you full EXP, it seemed. Once the yeti is dead, med up while the pet gets to full health. Once the pet is ready to go, kill the next yeti.<br>
<br>
You will have plenty of time between whole cave spawns to med up so do not med to full between each battle, it is just waste of time. If you are low on mana, just med enough to get mana for two bolt spells. I say this because once you clear the entire cave, there is a 10 minute or so break you have to med up. I usually practice my abjuration and divination in these breaks while I am waiting.<br>
<br>
At level 39, a whole cave clearing is a good chunk of a yellow bubble. At level 44 it is closer to 2 blues. Either way you slice it, the exp is awesome and the loot ROCKS. I was pulling in between 100-250pp per few hours. The yetis all drop between 5 gold and 5pp plus they have research components and Frosty Daturas(stackable flowers that sell for 1pp each). Most yetis drop 2 flowers. Also, you will get the occasional gem drop. I have gotten three peridots the whole time at this camp and a few flawless aquamarines as well as a few Golden Pendants or whatever that sell for 15pp!<br>
<br>
Another good thing about this camp is that there are always high level clerics running to and fro between the spires and KC, FV, FM, etc. Just do a /who cleric and send polite tells to the higher level ones asking if they are anywhere near you. You'll find a kind one who will gladly take a peridot and some plat to rez you if you do happen to die.<br>
<br>
Thanks for the information, fellas, it was a great camp. Came here with less than 400pp and left with 1705pp AFTER buying all my level 44 spells. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerlevels3943>Levels 39-43</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM AD SCRIPT -->
